From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: airoha: set kernel TEXT_OFFSET to 0x88000 on AN7563

The Airoha AN7563 / AN7552 (AArch32) bootloader stack reserves the
first ~256 KiB of DRAM for ATF (BL31 lives in 0x80003000-0x80035000
with adjacent TZRAM pads, see plat/ecnt/en7523/include/platform_def.h
in the en75xx-class ATF source). Vendor firmware therefore loads the
Linux kernel at 0x80088000, i.e. 0x88000 above the DRAM base, leaving
the entire ATF area untouched and giving an additional headroom band
for BL2 / NPU staging.

With the default ARM TEXT_OFFSET of 0x8000 the kernel would be linked
against PHYS_OFFSET + 0x8000 = 0x80008000 while the FIT loadaddr is
0x80088000. CONFIG_ARM_PATCH_PHYS_VIRT then back-computes PHYS_OFFSET
as stext_phys - TEXT_OFFSET = 0x80080000, which mismatches the DT
memory@80000000 node and turns __turn_mmu_on into a silent jump to
nowhere - no earlycon output, no panic.

Introduce a dedicated Kconfig sub-option SOC_AIROHA_AN7563 (rather
than keying off ARCH_AIROHA) so that EN7523 - which shares
arch/arm/Makefile but is a different OpenWrt sub-target with its own
verified layout - is not accidentally retargeted by this offset. The
new option is selected only by the OpenWrt an7563 sub-target config
(target/linux/airoha/an7563/config-6.12).

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm/Kconfig.platforms | 9 +++++++++
 arch/arm/Makefile          | 2 ++
 2 files changed, 11 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/Kconfig.platforms
+++ b/arch/arm/Kconfig.platforms
@@ -76,6 +76,15 @@ config ARCH_AIROHA
 	select HAVE_ARM_ARCH_TIMER
 	help
 	  Support for Airoha EN7523 SoCs
+
+config SOC_AIROHA_AN7563
+	bool "Airoha AN7563 / AN7552 (dual Cortex-A53 AArch32) layout"
+	depends on ARCH_AIROHA
+	help
+	  Select this when targeting the Airoha AN7563 / AN7552 SoC, which
+	  reserves the first 0x88000 bytes of DRAM for ATF (BL31 + TZRAM
+	  pads) and expects the kernel to be linked at that offset above
+	  the DRAM base instead of the ARM default 0x8000.
 
 config MACH_ASM9260
 	bool "Alphascale ASM9260"
--- a/arch/arm/Makefile
+++ b/arch/arm/Makefile
@@ -167,6 +167,8 @@ endif
 textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_QCOM_RESERVE_SMEM) := 0x00208000
 textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_MESON) := 0x00208000
 textofs-$(CONFIG_ARCH_AXXIA) := 0x00308000
+# Airoha AN7563 / AN7552: leave the first 0x88000 of DRAM to ATF
+textofs-$(CONFIG_SOC_AIROHA_AN7563) := 0x00088000
 
 # Machine directory name.  This list is sorted alphanumerically
 # by CONFIG_* macro name.
